## Post Type: Blog post opening paragraph
## Topic: Why we stopped calling it exercise

---

There's a word we don't use here. You'll notice it's missing from
everything we write and everything we say in our groups.

The word is "exercise."

Not because movement doesn't matter. It matters enormously.
But because "exercise" implies a transaction – effort in, results out.
What we're building is something else entirely.

A Tuesday that you'd cancel other things for.
People who notice when you're not there.
A version of yourself that you didn't know was still waiting.

That's not exercise. That has a different name.

---

## What makes this on-brand:
- Challenges an assumption immediately
- No defensive tone, no apology for being different
- Concrete image: "A Tuesday you'd cancel other things for"
- Ends on identity, not benefit
- Zero jargon, zero motivational clichés
